7/18/14<br>
<a name="tewksbury-nh"><b>Tewksbury, NH</b></a>
<p>
When did we start annexing chunks of Massachusetts? And can we give it back, or did Mass demand we take it off their hands?
<p>
<center><a href="http://www.wmur.com/money/market-basket-employees-to-protest-ceo-firing/27012082?absolute=true"><img src="tewksbury-nh.jpg"><br>
Click for WMUR misreport</a></center><p>
<p>
It's obviously <a href="index.html#wmur-guardians-of-the-official-proclamation">time to delete WMUR</a>  from my news bookmarks. The blindly reprint police press releases unquestioningly, misreport nonexeistent machine guns, <b>refuse</b> to make corrections when caught out...
<p>
...and fail basic geography. Meh. Maybe they can <a href="http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2014/07/16/tsa-dc-license-orlando-airport/12722415/">get jobs with the TSA</a>.
<p>
This sucks. WMUR was the last website I had left for routinely getting local news. But like the others I already dropped, I can't count on them to get <strike>basic facts</strike> <b>anything</b> right.
<p>
