<i>Members of a northeast Georgia SWAT team are "devastated" after a drug raid in which a flash-bang grenade landed in a 1-year-old's playpen, seriously injuring the child, the Habersham County sheriff said Friday.
<p>
The police officers involved have been called baby killers and received threats following the incident, Sheriff Joey Terrell said.
<p>
"All I can say is pray for the baby, his family <b>and for us</b>," he told CNN.</i><font size=2>(emphasis added - cb)</font></blockquote>
